1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an improved auto-encoder for feature extraction and classification, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The proposed method is applied to the benchmark dataset MNIST, which is a commonly used dataset in computer vision and pattern recognition. 
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses the use of neural networks, specifically auto-encoders, for feature extraction and classification. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an AI-based method for feature extraction and classification. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): Although not directly related to natural language processing, the proposed method could potentially be applied to text data for feature extraction and classification tasks.
